The paper deals with image-to-image translation and domain adaptation, which are topics commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed models involve the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) and feature alignment, which are also relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also includes experiments on image datasets, which could potentially fall under the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
